body:
> Verilator version:
```
Verilator 4.038 2020-07-11 rev v4.036-114-g0cd4a57ad
```
> Testcase
```systemverilog
//t_param_err.v
/* verilator lint_off DECLFILENAME */
module t;
/* verilator lint_on DECLFILENAME */
parameter p [1:0][7:0][7:0] = '{default:0};
initial begin
if (p[0][0][0] != 1'b0) $stop;
$write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
$finish;
end
endmodule
```
> Then translated by verilator with the following  command: _**verilator -Wall --sc t_param_err.v**_ , I meet a error like this:
```
%Error: t_param_err.v:7:15: Illegal assignment of constant to unpacked array
                          : ... In instance t
    7 |       if (p[0][0][0] != 1'b0) $stop;
      |               ^
%Error: Exiting due to 1 error(s)
```
> If the following statement is modified in this way, translated successfully by verilator.
```systemverilog
parameter p [1:0][7:0][7:0] = '{default:0}; 
```
> changed to
```systemverilog
parameter p [1:0][7:0][7:0] = '{default:'{default:'{default:0}}}; 
```
> I think it might be a bug, what's your opinion?
